# bijux-dna-core Docs Index

## Canonical entry
This is the canonical entry point for bijux-dna-core documentation.

## Public surface
Public modules are `contract`, `id_catalog`, `ids`, `metrics`, and `prelude`.

## Start here
- `CONTRACT_MAP.md` for what contracts exist and where they live.
- `CONTRACT_VERSIONING.md` for breaking-change rules and hashing stability.
- `BOUNDARIES.md` for what must never live in bijux-dna-core.

## Scope
- `SCOPE.md` for what belongs here (and what does not).
- `SSOT.md` for single-source-of-truth responsibilities.

## Effects
- `BOUNDARIES.md` for what core must never do (no execution, no network, no tool spawning).

## Boundaries
- `BOUNDARIES.md` for dependency rules and allowed imports.

## Extension Points
- `CHANGE_RULES.md` for safe extension guidelines and breaking-change rules.

## Architecture & scope
- `ARCHITECTURE.md` for module layout.

## Serialization & invariants
- `SERIALIZATION.md` for canonical JSON and hashing.
- `INVARIANTS.md` for contract invariants.

## Tests
- `TESTS.md` for the test map and fixture coverage.

## How to Test
- `TESTS.md` for the test map and fixture coverage.

[bijux-dna-db-ena]
# INDEX

## Scope
- ENA metadata query + download support for corpus materialization.

## Effects
- Network I/O to ENA endpoints.
- Filesystem writes under explicit output directories.

## Boundaries
- No pipeline planning.
- No tool execution orchestration.

## Extension Points
- Add filters/selection policies in model/client modules.
- Add transfer strategies in download module.

## How to Test
- Unit tests in `src/*`.
- Guardrails in `tests/guardrails.rs`.
- Contract docs in this directory.

## Documents
- [SCOPE.md](SCOPE.md)
- [ARCHITECTURE.md](ARCHITECTURE.md)
- [TESTS.md](TESTS.md)

